There is a quick example of how the XAML code can be shared between different views/windows. Create a `ResourceDictionary`, define the shared properties/styles/control templates, like this
```
&lt;ResourceDictionary xmlns=&quot;http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation&quot;
                    xmlns:x=&quot;http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml&quot;&gt;
	&lt;Style TargetType=&quot;{x:Type Label}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;Black&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;FontFamily&quot; Value=&quot;Segoe UI&quot; /&gt;
	&lt;/Style&gt;
	&lt;Style TargetType=&quot;{x:Type Button}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;Black&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;FontFamily&quot; Value=&quot;Segoe UI&quot; /&gt;
	&lt;/Style&gt;
	&lt;Style TargetType=&quot;{x:Type TextBox}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;Black&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;FontFamily&quot; Value=&quot;Segoe UI&quot; /&gt;
	&lt;/Style&gt;
	&lt;Style TargetType=&quot;{x:Type ScrollBar}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;Foreground&quot; Value=&quot;Black&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;FontFamily&quot; Value=&quot;Segoe UI&quot; /&gt;
	&lt;/Style&gt;
	&lt;Style TargetType=&quot;Label&quot; x:Key=&quot;TitleStyle&quot; BasedOn=&quot;{StaticResource {x:Type Label}}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;HorizontalContentAlignment&quot; Value=&quot;Center&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;VerticalContentAlignment&quot; Value=&quot;Center&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;HorizontalAlignment&quot; Value=&quot;Stretch&quot; /&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;VerticalAlignment&quot; Value=&quot;Stretch&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;Setter Property=&quot;FontSize&quot; Value=&quot;16&quot; /&gt;
	&lt;/Style&gt;
&lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
```
Than you can add this dictionary to App/Window resource dictionary to use them, like
```
&lt;Window.Resources&gt;
		&lt;ResourceDictionary&gt;
			&lt;ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries&gt;
				&lt;ResourceDictionary Source=&quot;Styles.xaml&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;/ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries&gt;
		&lt;/ResourceDictionary&gt;
&lt;/Window.Resources&gt;
```
Please, note that this is just a quick example to explain the idea. You can also look at [MSDN][1] to see explanation between `TargetType` and `x:Key` in styles


  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.windows.style.targettype?view=netframework-4.8

