Like what the error states, you cannot use a value as a type. What you can do is something like this.
```
export type UPDATE_SESSION_PROP = &#39;UPDATE_SESSION_PROP&#39;;

// This works
type UserEmailAction = {type: UPDATE_SESSION_PROP,
                        propName: &#39;currentUserEmail&#39;,
                        payload: string};
```


And the implementation of the second version actually has a different meaning. If means that you make `&#39;UPDATE_SESSION_PROP&#39;` as the only acceptable value for `type`
```
//This works becuase `UPDATE_SESSION_PROP` is considered Literal Type
type UserEmailAction = {type: &#39;UPDATE_SESSION_PROP&#39;,
                        propName: &#39;currentUserEmail&#39;,
                        payload: string};
```

[Literal Type - Flow](https://flow.org/en/docs/types/literals/)

